  "event": {
    "top_event": "Uncontrolled descent of construction hoist block",
    "incident_type": "Equipment Failure",
    "costs": "3390",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Driller shut down the drawworks to stop additional motion",
      "All operations stopped to investigate cause",
      "Safety stand down implemented",
      "Personnel instructed to avoid the area",
      "Safety assessment performed",
      "Damaged drill pipe joint and coupling taken out of service",
      "Construction hoist block coupling replaced"
    ],
    "summary": "On 28 September 2020 at approximately 0049 hours, while setting down single joint drill pipes onto the construction floor using the construction hoist block on the Noble Globetrotter I Drill Ship, the construction hoist block descended uncontrollably without input from the driller. The block continued its descent until it contacted the top of a drill pipe joint, applying approximately 50,000 pounds of pressure and causing the pipe to bow. The probable cause was determined to be failure of the mechanical coupling between the Forward Motor and Gearbox on the Construction Hoist Block.",
